{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"403f13f4-c904-44a5-a139-cab6a88e08d1","content":"## How it works\n\n| Concept | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Trigger** | Runs when you publish a GitHub Release |\n| **OIDC** | `id-token: write` lets the runner request a JWT proving the workflow's identity |\n| **Trusted Publisher** | nuget.org verifies the OIDC token matches your registered repo/workflow/environment — no `--api-key` needed |\n| **Environment** | `nuget-publish` adds approval gates and branch restrictions |\n\n## Setting the package version\n\nTag your release (e.g., `v1.2.3`), then derive the version in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<Version>1.2.3</Version>\n```\n\nOr pass it dynamically:\n\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet pack src/MyLib/MyLib.csproj -c Release -o ./artifacts -p:Version=${GITHUB_REF_NAME#v}\n```\n\n## Key points\n\n- **No secrets to rotate** — authentication is based on the workflow's OIDC identity\n- **Environment protection rules** prevent unauthorized publishes\n- **Scoped trust** — only the specified repo, workflow file, and environment can push your package","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93334da6-c634-4be0-8f2a-26217127cde1","outputTokens":282,"requestId":"6C4E:B0194:D56FBA:10A059A:6A012A69"},"id":"5d5707a8-0ab8-4ad5-bf23-3b4789c39333","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:01:37.242Z","parentId":"8edb3f57-00a1-4d2e-998a-98438b0b8928"}
